{
  "stem": "4361.8",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my other brother is surely not alive, the Danube. 1945, December-- or maybe it was 1946, January-- it doesn't really matter-- at night, somebody knocks on the window.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We run, and I look out, and it's my brother Alex.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SIGHS] So there was some sort of an evilness.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What had happened, he was not shot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he was put in a transport, and he himself is going to give a testimony soon.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was eventually sent to a work camp in-- called [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Einegamme, ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Einegamme, ?] and he was liberated by the British.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, he began looking at all kinds of Red Cross lists for names, and he found no names.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Clearly, he-- the Russians didn't keep lists.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he had no particular compunction to come back home until somebody-- and this was at the end of December 1945 or early January 1946-- met him.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This somebody left-- had left Sighet and met my brother somewhere in western Europe and said, hey, Alex, do you know your sister is back home in Sighet?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's when he came back, and that's how we met.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And just as far as my brother is concerned, he stayed for a couple of months.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He stayed for-- for-- to the end of the year.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, he went back because then already, the-- the Israelis that-- he eventually volunteered the-- into the Haganah during the War of Independence.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As far as I'm concerned, this-- it was a very drab life because the Communist Party was after me to join and-- the Romanian Communist Party.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was young, and they needed cadres.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I didn't really want to because I didn't know much about Communism, but I didn't want to-- or any -isms.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
